'''''Star Wars Insider'' 57''' is the fifty-seventh issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was released to newsstands on [[December 4]], [[2001]]. Issue 57 was the first overseen by chief editor [[Dave Gross]].

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"[[Rebel Rumblings]]"
*"Episode II [[Prequel Update]] with [[Rick McCallum]]" {{C|by [[Dan Madsen]] and [[Robin D. Laws]]}}
*"[[Star News]]"
*"[[Comics Link]]" &mdash; Adapting [[Star Wars: Jedi Quest (comic series)|Jedi Quest]] {{C|by Daniel Wallace}}
*"[[Bookshelf]]" &mdash; The [[Shelly Shapiro|New Jedi Editor]] {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*"[[Gamescape]]" &mdash; Being Obi-Wan Kenobi {{C|by [[Elliot Chin]]}}
*"[[HoloNet (Insider)|HoloNet]]" &mdash; How to Build Your Own ''Star Wars'' Website {{C|by [[Paul Ens]]}}
*"[[Set Piece]]: Imperial Star Destroyer" {{C|by [[Chris Reiff]] & [[Chris Trevas]]}}
*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" &mdash; On the Circuit Comprehending Collectibles {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet]]}}
*"[[Crossword (department)|Crossword]]" &mdash; Title Shock {{C|by [[Michael Selinker|Mike Selinker]]}}
*"[[Dear 2-1B]]"

===Features===
*"[[Temuera Morrison: Once & Future Warrior]]" {{C|by [[Scott Chernoff]]}}
*:<small>Jango who? The original bounty hunter arrives with ''Attack of the Clones'', and New Zealander sensation Temuera Morrison brings him to life.</small>
*"[[Daniel Logan: Logan's Run]]" {{C|by Scott Chernoff}}
*:<small>What could be cooler than playing the role of young Anakin Skywalker? Daniel Logan tells the ''Insider'' what it was like to play a four-foot-tall Boba Fett.</small>
*"[[Down Underworld: Leeanna Walsman]]" {{C|by [[Michael J. Ryan]]}}
*:<small>Never heard of Leeanna Walsman? Where've you been living, the Northern Hemisphere? This talented actress might just be the bounty-hunting breakout of Episode II.</small>
*"[[Who's Who in the New Jedi Order]]" {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace]]}}
*:<small>From ''Vector Prime'' to the world-shattering events of ''Star by Star'', who are the new heroes, scoundrels, and villains of the ''Star Wars'' Expanded Universe?</small>
*"[[Aurra Sing's Convention Diary]]" {{C|by [[Michonne Bourriague]]}}
*:<small>The alter-ego of the notorious bounty hunter sheds light on the dark underbelly of... conventions?</small>

